Cheliped (
Fig. 1I
). Basis divided unequally by sclerite, shorter than carpus. Merus triangular with one ventral seta. Carpus longer than propodus including fixed finger, with two ventral setae. Propodus with one seta near dactylus insertion on inner margin. Fixed finger with two ventral setae, three on inner margin, and with four prominent sharp denticles on inner margin. Dactylus as long as fixed finger.

